<B><FONT SIZE=+1>NETWORK MODEL</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>cost of storage servers: major issue</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>purpose: minimize costs to make MOD servers affordable</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>how to achieve that?</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>hierarchical solutions</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>caching</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>sharing</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Hierarchical network model (<a
href="c10afig/f10-5.JPG">fig. 10-5</a>)</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>international network -></FONT></LI>
</UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; national backbone networks
-></FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; regional backbone
networks -></FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; access (or neighborhood)
networks -></FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; homes</FONT>
<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>the costs in this hierarchy can be reduced by exploiting
spatial and temporal locality properties</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1><I>info/program caching</I>: store documents that are likely
to
be requested often on the neighborhood servers and less frequently requested
documents in higher levels of the hierarchy</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>
